velocity over time: $\dot{\mathbf{P}} = (V_X, V_Y, V_Z)^\mathsf{T}$. At
each time instant, $t$, the point location will be
$\mathbf{P}(t) = (X+V_Xt, Y+V_Yt, Z+V_Zt)^\mathsf{T}$, and its 2D
projection: 

$$\begin{aligned}
x(t) &= f \frac{X + V_X t}{Z + V_Z t}\\

